| `src/lib/org-list.ts` | 637-641 | `ContextError("Project", "'X' is an org...")` | `ResolutionError("'X'", "is an organization, not a project", ...)` |
| `src/lib/org-list.ts` | 649-653 | `ContextError("Project", "No project 'X' found...\n\nTry: ...")` | `ResolutionError("Project 'X'", "not found", ...)` |
| `src/commands/project/list.ts` | 515-519 | Same pattern | Same fix |
| `src/commands/issue/list.ts` | 375-378 | `ContextError("Projects", "No projects found in org 'X'.")` | `ResolutionError("Organization 'X'", "has no projects", ...)` |
| `src/commands/issue/list.ts` | 903-908 | Multiline note in command | Split: simple `ContextError` + note in alternatives |
| `src/lib/db/pagination.ts` | 195 | `ContextError("Pagination cursor", "No saved cursor...")` | `ValidationError("No saved cursor for this query. Run without --cursor first.")` |

### Fix 3: `event view` — handle issue URLs gracefully + fix error message

**File:** `src/commands/event/view.ts` lines 115-130

Currently when a user passes an issue URL (has `issueId` but no `eventId`), the error is:
```
Event ID in URL (use a URL like /issues/{id}/events/{eventId}/) is required.
```

**Fix:** When `parseSentryUrl` returns an `issueId` but no `eventId`, use `getLatestEvent(org, issueId)` to fetch the latest event for that issue and proceed normally. Log an info message like: `"Fetching latest event for issue {issueId}..."`

This is a better UX — the user clearly wants to see an event, and we can get one. The `getLatestEvent(orgSlug, issueId)` API already exists in `src/lib/api/events.ts:27`.

```typescript
// In parsePositionalArgs, replace lines 125-130:
if (urlParsed.issueId && !urlParsed.eventId) {
  // Issue URL — we'll fetch the latest event from this issue
  return {
    eventId: `latest:${urlParsed.issueId}`,  // sentinel for the caller
    targetArg: `${urlParsed.org}/`,
    issueId: urlParsed.issueId,
  };
}
```

The actual latest-event fetch happens in `viewCommand.func()` — when `issueId` is present in the parsed result, call `getLatestEvent(org, issueId)` instead of `getEvent(org, project, eventId)`. This avoids needing a project slug entirely.

